The GeoJSON file should meet the {{link}} specification.
The name of the file should be 'Facilities.geojson'.
All the features in the file should have geometries of the same type (i.e. All should be points, or all should be multipolygons and so on).
The coordinates should be in the valid range of Latitude & Longitude (Valid range for Latitude is -90 to +90 & Valid range of Longitude is -180 to +180).
All the features in the file should have properties with the same set of keys.
The file features should have important keys such as 'Facility code', 'Facility name', 'Facility type', 'Facility status', 'Capacity', 'Boundary code'.

In the Properties object, the values for fields which represent a Numeric Value, should not be quoted with double quotes, (i.e. facility code of 10,000 should be represented as “facility code” : 10000 and not “facility code” : “10,0000”
The user should zip up all the files in .zip format, and upload them into the system. At a minimum, the system needs .shp, .shx & .dbf files zipped.
The name of the zip file should be 'Facilities.zip'.
The shapefile should be in the WGS 84 lat-long coordinate system for the system to accept.
The coordinates should be in the valid range of Latitude & Longitude (Valid range for Latitude is -90 to +90 & Valid range of Longitude is -180 to +180).
The shape file should have the important data points such as 'Facility code', 'Facility name', 'Facility type', 'Facility status', 'Capacity', 'Boundary code'.
The total size of the zipped file should not exceed 2 GB.
All the fields are mandatory and can't be empty, except the Latitude and Longitude fields.
The Latitude & Longitude fields should have data in Degree Decimal and Degree Minute Seconds (Value should be 12.3455 & not 12° 20' 43.7994').

You are on the BI Clients tab in the characteristic editing screen in the BW modeling tools. You have chosen Shapes or Shapes and Point Data as the geographical type.
Choose Upload Shapefiles under Actions. Choose Go. The BW/4 backend opens.
Select your shapefiles. You need the following three shapefiles: .dbf, .shp, .shx. The shapefiles must be in the Spatial Reference ID 4326 and should all have the same name before the ending.
Choose Update Geotable under Actions. Choose Go. You can choose either Delta Update or Full Update.

The uploaded shapes are transformed and stored in SRID (Spatial Reference ID) 3857. It is therefore not possible to use shapes in SAC if they exceed the limitations of this spatial reference system. This means that they must not have degrees of latitude exceeding 85.06° and -85.06°.

You have added a column or field with the characteristic name to the shapefiles that you want to load shapes for. If using compounding characteristics, you have added multiple columns. More Information:
To update the geotable with shapes that are uploaded to the Business Document Server, you need SAP HANA 2.0 Rev 45.
